Definition.WordDefinition: Craw \Craw\ (kr[add]), n. [Akin to D. kraag neck, collar, G. kragen, Sw. kr[aum]fva craw, Dan. kro, and possibly to Gr. ???? (E. bronchus), or bro`chqos throat. [root]25. Cf. {Crag} neck.] (Zo["o]l.) (a) The crop of a bird. (b) The stomach of an animal. [1913 Webster]
craw n : a pouch in many birds and some lower animals that resembles a stomach for storage and preliminary maceration of food [syn: {crop}]
